cast.overview: Joe Gideon is at the top of the heap, one of the most successful directors and choreographers in musical theater. But he can feel his world slowly collapsing around him - his obsession with work has almost destroyed his personal life, and only his bottles of pills keep him going.
cast.title: All That Jazz

details.biography: Susan Brooks was an actress who founded her entertainment career success with roles in film. Brooks found her beginnings in film with roles in "Invitation to the Wedding" (1973) with Ralph Richardson and "All That Jazz" (1979) with Roy Scheider. She then acted in "Captain Stirrick" (1982), "Dan Turner, Hollywood Detective" (1989-1990) and the Jason James Richter adventure sequel "Free Willy 2: The Adventure Home" (1995). More recently, Brooks acted in the comedic drama "Zacharia Farted" (1998) with Colin Cunningham.
details.name: Susan Brooks
